## Bug Report: `processItems` Function

### The Bug

**File:** `/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775348217108-3k0ndk/src/utils.ts`

**Exact Line with Bug:** Line 7
```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {
```

**What the Bug Is:** The loop condition uses `i < items.length - 1` instead of `i < items.length`. This is a classic off-by-one error that causes the last element (at index `items.length - 1`) to never be processed.

### The Fix

Change line 7 from:
```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {
```

To:
```typescript
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

---

## Full Content of `processItems` Function

```typescript
export function processItems(items: string[]): string[] {
  const results: string[] = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {
    results.push(items[i].toUpperCase());
  }
  return results;
}
```

